nt right, for \"\u2183\"-shaped curve it would point left, and if you join them together into \"S\"-shaped curver, it has to flip at the joint point. For \"I\"-shaped curve (line segment) only T vector is well-defined, and N would be zero (a math's way of saying \"I have no way to pick direction, they are all the same\"). Of course, it's not a problem if you just set curve's TNB vectors manually or using some parameterized expression but, if it's just some bezier path through a bunch of points the user just selected at random, you would be in trouble.\n","created_at":"2016-11-19T12:42:08.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10160#issuecomment-261711752","id":261711752,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10160","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI2MTcxMTc1Mg==","updated_at":"2016-11-19T12:42:08.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/261711752","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/242577?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/makc","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI0MjU3Nw==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"makc","type":"User","id":242577,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"In fact, how do you even get a vertex position in that case